Rating: 3
This was simple and delicious. The feta I used was strong and salty - I used 2 oz more feta than called for, only 1 1/4 cup milk (I ran out!), and no dill. (Not on purpose - farmer's market had zero dill and I was hungry so I forged ahead without it!) The matzohs wouldn't all fit into the soaking dish at the same time (especially with too little milk to cover them) so I soaked them just a couple at a time. This made it take a little longer prep time, but I think it may have been better than adding more liquid to cover them. It held together beautifully when cut, nice and firm. And I can only imagine how lovely this is when you have fresh dill. Initially I was worried by all the variance in the reviews about what people did or didn't like - now my impression that a lot is personal preference, how much you expect it to taste like spanakopita, and some of it is what kind of feta was used. Feta can be strong, or nearly flavorless, depending on what type you buy.

