Rating: 4
All of my Passover Seder guests really enjoyed this spinach and matzo pie, which my son dubbed "Spana-matzo-ka." I followed the recipe nearly exactly, the only exception being that I used 8 instead of 6 ounces of feta. I did soak the matzo and was glad I did, as the moisture helped keep the exposed matzo parts from burning. I especially appreciated being able to assemble the pie a day in advance and refrigerate it until just before baking, which made the day of the Seder significantly less hectic. I also liked the way the pie's Mediterranean flavors complemented those of the Catalan-style Sardine Escabèche, also on this site, which I served as a first course. I don't know how well the pie will hold up after baking, because I have no leftovers to test; my guests devoured the entire panful. This will definitely be a Passover staple.

